caption.p: Influence of blood and oropharyngeal contamination on percentages of the different nucleated cell subsets in BALs from healthy macaques. (A) All BAL samples, regardless of blood or oropharyngeal contamination. (B) Cell subsets considering blood and oropharyngeal contaminations. Each dot is representative of one specimen. Bars, medians Â± 95% confidence interval; OP, oropharyngeal; Contam., contamination. * P-value < 0.05.
